article.headline: Wright St. 59, Loyola 47
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- DaShawn Wood scored 13 points Saturday to lead Wright State to a 59-47 victory over Loyola of Chicago. Trailing 35-25 at the start of the second half, Loyola (13-9, 4-5 Horizon) ran off eight points, six on back-to-back three-pointers from Blake Schilb, to make it 35-33. Wright State (14-8, 7-2 Horizon) countered with a 9-2 run of its own, to build its lead to 44-35. J.R Blount made a pair of foul shots with 2:34 left to bring the Ramblers within four, 51-47, but Loyola missed its final five field-goal attempts and the Raiders scored the final eight points of the contest. Loyola started the game by scoring the first five points, and led 13-11 five minutes into the game. But the Rambler offense turned sluggish, and the Raiders held Loyola scoreless for nearly six minutes to turn a 16-15 lead into a 26-15 advantage. Todd Brown scored 10 points for Wright State. Schilb had 14 points and 10 rebounds for Loyola. Leon Young and Majak Kou tallied eight points apiece. Blount finished the game with eight points.
